    "They expressed that their engagement in the IDC course was driven by their desire to make progress in these areas, and they believed that responsible students should naturally possess skills related to IDC.",
    "Participant 13 specifically noted that the concept of learning interest aligns with the characteristics of the IDC theoretical loop circulation, emphasizing its significance as a prerequisite for effective engagement.",
    "Participant 13 Participant 1 and 8 shared their perspectives on the teacher support provided in the IDC.",
    "They expressed that the high level of teacher support in IDC compensated for the cumulative proficiency and self-efficacy.",
    "In particular, Participant 8 emphasized the importance of personal interest in language acquisition, stating that one's ability to maintain and enhance target language skills is closely linked to their level of interest in the learning process."
